{"TopicId":213550,"ForumId":196,"TopicTitle":"Truss\u0027, nose cones, and some engines freak out when attaching to truss hubs while rotating the camera.","CreatedByName":"Space-Doggo","CreatedById":226747,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T06:23:46Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Space-Doggo","CreatedById":226747,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T06:23:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKSP Version: 0.1.0.0.20892\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS: Windows 11 (22H2)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECPU: AMD R9 5900X\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EGPU: EVGA RTX 3080TI\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ERAM: 32GB DDR4\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003EDescription of bug\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003EWhen trying to add truss\u0027, nose cones, or some engines\u00A0around a hub, it will result in very rapid attaching and \u003C/b\u003E\u003Cb\u003Edetaching\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cb style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0of said part while rotating the camera around the rocket.\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EExpected Behavior\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EPart would either stay attached or detach from the attachment node on the hub while rotating camera.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EObserved Behavior\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003EPart rapidly snaps to and from the hubs attachment node while rotating.\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESteps to Replicate\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003EPlace a hub in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003EGrab a truss, nosecone, or an engine\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003EBring part near hub attachment node\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003ERight click and rotate camera\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EFixes / Workarounds: N/A\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EMods: None\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(45,49,52);font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOther Notes:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SJRUumGcagc\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EHere is a video showing the issue.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}